      "writtenOn": "2026-06-22T22:15:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This method should belong to a `BatchApplyObjectCommand` which is able to work on a set of apply object commands.\n\nWe now have a misleading class organisation here:\n- `ApplyObjectCommand` doesn\u0027t work on a single command but on a batch of commands\n- `BatchApplyObjectCommand` doesn\u0027t exist\n\nWhat I believe we should do instead is:\n\na) Create a brand-new command called `BatchApplyObjectCommand` which implements the transactional execution of multiple apply objects in a single batch\n\nb) Have the `ApplyObjectAction` call the `BatchApplyObjectCommand` with a set of one apply object action.\n\nIn terms of execution, we should first implement and run it side by side with the existing code. Then we can make a separate change to remove the legacy `ApplyObjectCommand` and use the new implementation.\n\nAt the moment, the class names are misleading, as the single command actually manages a batch of commands.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 42
